---
title: Portobello Burgers and Sweet Potato Fries with Tomato Onion Jam and Avocado
description: Tired of eating the same old veggie burger? Yeah, us too. That’s why we’ve upgraded the dish with a hearty portobello and a tangy tomato onion jam that’s a zillion times better than boring ketchup. To make your fries extra crispy, do what our chefs do and preheat the oven with the baking sheet inside. Trust us, it’s a game changer.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/plt-w38-cfd06d33.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/plt-w38-68faf5bb.pdf
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 667 kcal
  fat: 32 g
  saturated fat: 4 g
  carbohydrates: 87 g
  sugar: 20 g
  protein: 13 g
  fiber: 15 g
  sodium: 333 mg
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/portobello-burgers-and-sweet-potato-fries-57b5bbc37417fe35568b4568
time required: 30 minutes
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the oven to 425 degrees. Peel the @sweet potatoes{12%oz} and cut into ½-inch sticks (like French fries). Toss on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place in the #oven{} for about ~{25%minutes}, tossing once, until golden brown and crispy.

Meanwhile, core, seed, and dice @roma tomato{1}(diced). Thinly slice the other @roma tomato{1}(thinly sliced). Halve, peel, and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(thinly sliced). Drizzle the @portobello mushrooms{8%oz} with @olive oil{drizzle}, and season on all sides with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place on another baking sheet with the sweet potatoes and bake ~{10-12%minutes}, until tender.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle} in a #medium pan{} over medium heat. Add the onion and diced tomato. Cook, stirring often, until jammy, for ~{10-15%minutes}. Add a splash of @water{} if the jam becomes too thick. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

While the jam cooks, halve, pit, and thinly slice the @avocado{1}(thinly sliced). Halve the @brioche buns{2}, and place in the oven to toast about ~{5%minutes}.

Assemble the burgers: Spread the buns with @mayonnaise{1%jar} and the tomato onion jam. Top with the portobellos, sliced tomato, and a few slices of avocado. Serve with the sweet potato fries on the side. Enjoy!